FInd prev and next great element using stack.

given array[1,3,2,4]
o/p- [3,4,4,-1]
In this question we have been given an array and we have to find out the next great element if we can't find then nxt element we have to right as -1.
Sln: let's say i have to check the nxt great element in right for number 3 in array so for that the next elements 2 and 4 should be in the array right. And on top 2 should 
be there and then at last 4. By keeping that in mind below     

fun findNextGreaterElement(arr: IntArray): IntArray { // find next greatest element to right.
    val n = arr.size
    val result = IntArray(n)
    val stack = ArrayDeque<Int>()
    for (i in n - 1 downTo 0) {
        while (stack.isNotEmpty() && stack.last() <= arr[i]) {
            stack.removeLast()
        }
        result[i] = if (stack.isEmpty()) -1 else stack.last()
        stack.addLast(arr[i])
    }
    return result
}

fun findNextGreaterElementToLeft(arr: IntArray): IntArray{ // find previous greatest element.

    val n = arr.size
    val res = IntArray(n)
    val stack = ArrayDeque<Int>()

    for(i in 0..n-1){
        while(stack.size > 0 && stack.last() <= arr[i]){
            stack.removeLast()
        }
        res[i] = if(stack.size == 0) -1 else stack.last()
        stack.addLast(arr[i])
    }

    return res
}
